HEADWORD: Pliancy
<hw>Pli"an*cy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The quality or state
of being pliant in sense; <as>as, the <ex>pliancy</ex> of a
rod</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧Avaunt all specious <xex>pliancy</xex> of
mind.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Wordsworth.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

